                              Neon Installation
		              =================

              +-----------------------------------------------+
              | This code is in a *pre-alpha* state. Don't    |
              | even try to think about using Neon for very   |
              | critical data.                                |
              +-----------------------------------------------+

To build NEON, it just follows the simple 'make' and 'make install', and that
just installs NEON into your ~/bin/ directory. You can also do a global
installation like so:

	$ make PREFIX=/usr install
	$ # or PREFIX=/usr/local

NEON currently has no dependencies.
